<HEADLINE>
BRAZIELS, MCDONALD CAN'T PLAY THIS SEASON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JENNIFER FLOYD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH _ When TCU's highly touted football recruiting class
reports today, two players will be missing and another won't be
eligible to play this season.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive backs Jerome and Jerrod Braziel of Dunbar High School
met with Horned Frogs coach Dennis Franchione yesterday to tell him
they didn't qualify academically and didn't plan to enroll until
January. Linebacker LaMarcus McDonald from Waco High will report
but won't be academically eligible. He will be admitted as a
partial qualifier.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're disappointed,'' said Jerrod Braziel, who along with his
brother just recently found out they wouldn't be eligible. ``We
committed ourselves to TCU. Now, we're going to work hard to get
there.''
</P>
<P>
   The Braziels didn't make the minimum scores required by the NCAA
on the standardized tests to be eligible. They said they were close
and would spend the fall semester working to get the necessary
scores, including taking SAT and ACT preparatory classes.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is no doubt that Jerrod and Jerome will be with it
sometime,'' Franchione said. ``I still feel really good about this
group.''
</P>
<P>
   TCU signed 21 players during recruiting, and the other 19,
including McDonald, are expected to report today. The freshmen will
begin practice tomorrow night before beginning two-a-day practices
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   As a partial qualifier, McDonald can practice with the team but
is ineligible to play. He will be eligible to play next fall and
will be a sophomore athletically. The lost year of eligibility can
be gained back if McDonald is on course to graduate.
</P>
<P>
   TCU athletic director Eric Hyman said the school has a policy
against admitting partial qualifiers but reviews students on a
case-by-case basis. The case first has to be approved by Hyman and
then is passed on to the provost for approval. McDonald's case was
approved.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, we are disappointed that the class isn't
complete,'' Franchione said. ``But this is a temporary setback.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
