DRUGS-WEB _ Eric MacIver did not get his predicted $1 million bid
for the Internet domain name Drugs.com, but he's hardly
disappointed. An undisclosed bidder pledged to pay $823,456 Friday
for the right to use Drugs.com, which made the 21-year-old MacIver
financially healthier than he was three months ago when he acquired
the name _ for considerably less money. BY ROBBIE SHERWOOD. Story
