<P>
   HERBERT-COLUMN _ The death toll from the heat that scorched much
of the country from mid-July to the early days of August has
reached 271. The states that fared worst were Illinois, with 120
fatalities, and Missouri, with 61. Get used to it. By Bob Herbert.
</P>
<P>
   DOWD-COLUMN (Sioux Center, Iowa) _ When he walks through the
door of the party room at the Pizza Ranch, I realize I'm glad to
see Bob Dole. A girl can get pretty desperate sitting around a mall
in an outpost of northern Iowa. By Maureen Dowd.
</P>
