<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CLASSICAL-MUSIC-KIDS-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BUM-BUM-BA-BUM: EINE KLEINE BUS-TERMINAL-CLEARING MUSIC 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 (bl)  
 By DAVID WALLIS   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   On a muggy Monday night in July, some 80,000 classical music
fans ignored forecast thundershowers and flocked to New York's
